<subSubSection id="C35B53C89E7AFFBDB7E7F8FBFE186F9D" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="13" pageNumber="412" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BFE00439E7AFFBDB7E7F8FBFB4A6F0D" blockId="13.[151,1437,1833,2040]" lastBlockId="14.[151,1436,151,465]" lastPageId="14" lastPageNumber="413" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E7AFFBEB7E7F8FBFE71690F" authorityName="Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,480,1833,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Compsibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="412" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vandenberghei">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7AFFBEB7E7F8FBFE71690F" box="[151,480,1833,1859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Compsibidion vandenberghei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on 
<specimenCount id="9D47CBCA9E7AFFBEB585F8F8FCEC690F" box="[757,893,1833,1860]" pageId="13" pageNumber="412" type="female">two females</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F35640D39E7AFFBEB4B1F8FBFBA5690F" box="[961,1076,1833,1859]" name="Nicaragua" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Nicaragua</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4985CEA19E7AFFBEB332F8FBFB7E6908" box="[1090,1263,1833,1860]" country="Nicaragua" name="Nueva Segovia" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Nueva Segovia</collectingRegion>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD07DB29E7AFFBEB275F8FBFF45692B" author="Heffern, D. J. &amp; Santos-Silva, A. &amp; Nascimento, F. E. L." pageId="13" pageNumber="412" pagination="525 - 540" refId="ref11661" refString="Heffern, D. J., Santos-Silva, A. &amp; Nascimento, F. E. L. (2018) New species, redescriptions, and new records on Mexican and Central American Cerambycidae (Coleoptera). Zootaxa, 4446 (4), 525 - 540. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4446.4.6" type="journal article" year="2018">
Heffern 
<emphasis id="B935DC519E7AFFBEB214F8F8FA04690F" box="[1380,1429,1833,1859]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
). We examined another female from 
<collectingCountry id="F35640D39E7AFFBEB500F89FFD78692B" box="[624,745,1869,1895]" name="Guatemala" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E7AFFBEB589F89FFCDD692B" box="[761,844,1869,1895]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), and in comparison with the type material (
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E7AFFBEB248F89FFA0D692B" box="[1336,1436,1869,1895]" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">holotype</typeStatus>
illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E7AFFBEB65CF8A3FD9069C0" box="[300,513,1905,1932]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Figs 31, 33 and 35</figureCitation>
), the female examined has the body slightly wider, scape shorter and stouter (
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E7AFFBEB21FF8A3FF2769E3" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
), flagellomeres slightly thicker, femora slightly thicker, yellowish lateral macula on the anterior third of the elytron closed adjacent to the epipleura (it is open in the 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E7AFFBEB460F86BFCE76998" box="[784,886,1977,2004]" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">holotype</typeStatus>
), black anterior elytral macula closer to the black transverse band (
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E7AFFBEB629F80FFE3F69BB" box="[345,430,2013,2039]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="412">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), transverse black macula on posterior half of the elytron arched upward close to suture (
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E79FFBDB7D0FF45FF656EFD" box="[160,244,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
), and procoxal cavities slightly open behind (it is closed in the 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E79FFBDB4B7FF45FBBF6EFE" box="[967,1070,151,178]" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">holotype</typeStatus>
). However, these types of variations also occur in other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E79FFBDB553FF69FD516E99" authorityName="Thomson" authorityYear="1864" box="[547,704,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Compsibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E79FFBDB553FF69FD516E99" box="[547,704,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">Compsibidion</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as for example, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C417BC09E79FFBDB4EEFF69FB476E9A" authority="(Thomson, 1867)" baseAuthorityName="Thomson" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[926,1238,187,214]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Compsibidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="413" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanum">
<emphasis id="B935DC519E79FFBDB4EEFF69FB9B6E98" box="[926,1034,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">C. vanum</emphasis>
(Thomson, 1867)
</taxonomicName>
. Additionally, the upper eye lobes (
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E79FFBDB628FF0DFE3B6EB5" box="[344,426,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">Fig. 34</figureCitation>
) in the female from 
<collectingCountry id="F35640D39E79FFBDB5E4FF0DFC9C6EB5" box="[660,781,223,249]" name="Guatemala" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
have three rows of ommatidia, while in the 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E79FFBDB272FF0DFAF56EB5" box="[1282,1380,223,249]" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">holotype</typeStatus>
they have four rows (
<figureCitation id="137A1CC69E79FFBDB63DFED1FE0E6F51" box="[333,415,258,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 30–35" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1691,1715]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetId="figure-170@14.[151,1436,489,1668]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 30–35. Compsibidion vandenberghei Heffern, Santos-Silva &amp; Nascimento, 2018. 30-31) Dorsal habitus; 30) Female from Guatemala; 31) Holotype female. 32–33) Scape: 32) Female from Guatemala; 33) Holotype female. 34-35) Upper eye lobe: 34) Female from Guatemala; 35) Holotype female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6538443" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6538443/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
). However, in the female 
<typeStatus id="54FABEE19E79FFBDB5CEFED1FCB06F51" box="[702,801,259,285]" pageId="14" pageNumber="413">paratype</typeStatus>
, the left upper eye lobe has four rows of ommatidia, with a single ommatidium in the fourth row, and the right upper eye lobe has three rows of ommatidia.
